<paragraph id="8BD436C2873FAA2046A0FA9FDE4DAC7F" blockId="36.[189,1399,1388,1627]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
It is not clear from the original description how many females were used by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B33873FAA204236FA9EDF91AFA2" author="Cockerell" box="[1067,1265,1388,1415]" firstAuthor="Cockerell" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="167 - 221" refId="ref19848" refString="Cockerell T. D. A. 1919. Bees in the collection of the United States National Museum. 3. Proceedings of the United States National Museum 55: 167 - 221. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 00963801.55 - 2264.167" type="journal article" year="1919">Cockerell (1919)</bibRefCitation>
to describe this subspecies. However, it was apparently based on a single specimen collected by Melbourne A. Carriker in Aroa city, northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="F37C7652873FAA204477FA41D987AFE8" box="[618,743,1459,1485]" name="Venezuela" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus id="54D08860873FAA204536FA41D8F2AFE8" box="[811,914,1459,1485]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">holotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation id="13502A47873FAA2045B8FA41D89DAFEB" box="[933,1021,1459,1486]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="37.[189,232,759,785]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,264,719]" captionTargetId="figure@37.[189,1398,264,719]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="Fig. 26. Centris bimaculata carrikeri Cockerell, 1919, holotype, â™€ (NMNH; USNM ENT 00534188). A. Frontal view. B. Habitus, lateral view. Scale bars: A = 1 mm; B = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3723000" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3723000/files/figure.png" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
) is currently housed at 
<collectionCode id="ED7AAE07873FAA204300FA41DE17AFE8" box="[1309,1399,1459,1485]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/142r-0w94" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="Museum">NMNH</collectionCode>
and has the following data label: Aroa Venez [printed]\ Dec. 16.10 [handwritten]\ MACarriker collector [printed]\ on 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41873FAA20474FFA08DAF0AC31" box="[338,400,1530,1556]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Aster" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
