</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD436C2873FAA2046A0F8D3DF27ADCE" blockId="36.[189,1399,1824,2027]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41873FAA2046A0F8D3DAC3AD1F" box="[189,419,1824,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claripennis">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0873FAA2046A0F8D3DAC3AD1F" box="[189,419,1824,1851]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Centris claripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was erroneously described from 
<collectingRegion id="49AFF820873FAA204522F8D3D8DDAD1F" box="[831,957,1824,1851]" country="Brazil" name="Sao Paulo" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">SÃ£o Paulo</collectingRegion>
, southeastern 
<collectingCountry id="F37C7652873FAA204276F8D2DFD6AD1F" box="[1131,1206,1824,1850]" name="Brazil" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. Its distribution range in South America includes 
<collectingCountry id="F37C7652873FAA204451F8B6D9A3AD7B" box="[588,707,1860,1886]" name="Colombia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F37C7652873FAA2044CDF8B6D82CAD7B" box="[720,844,1860,1886]" name="Venezuela" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F37C7652873FAA204596F8B6DFE3AD7B" box="[907,1155,1860,1886]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Trinidad and Tobago</collectingCountry>
(unpubl. data). This species was erroneously proposed as a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41873FAA204599F895DFACADA4" authority="Lepeletier, 1841" authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[900,1228,1895,1921]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscata">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0873FAA204599F895D89FADA4" box="[900,1023,1895,1921]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">C. fuscata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B33873FAA204214F895DFACADA4" author="Lepeletier" box="[1033,1228,1895,1921]" firstAuthor="Lepeletier" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refId="ref21082" refString="Lepeletier A. L. M. 1841. Histoire naturelle des Insectes. Hymenopteres. Vol. II. Librairie encyclopedique de Roret, Paris." type="book" year="1841">Lepeletier, 1841</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFFA4B33873FAA2042C3F895DB9DAD81" author="Moure" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Moure" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="83 - 142" refId="ref21502" refString="Moure J. S., Melo G. A. R. &amp; Vivallo F. 2007. Centridini Cockerell &amp; Cockerell. In: Moure J. S., Urban D. &amp; Melo G. A. R. (orgs) Catalogue of Bees (Hymenoptera, Apoidea) in the Neotropical Region: 83 - 142. Sociedade Brasileira de Entomologia, Curitibrazil." type="book chapter" year="2007">
Moure 
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0873FAA204324F89ADE17ADA4" box="[1337,1399,1895,1921]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
). The study of the 
<typeStatus id="54D08860873FAA2047FDF879D973AD80" box="[480,531,1931,1957]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">type</typeStatus>
specimens of both species allows removing the former species from the synonymy of the latter, proposing its revalidation. Both sexes of 
<taxonomicName id="4C6B4D41873FAA2045A4F85CDF00ADE2" box="[953,1120,1965,1992]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="claripennis">
<emphasis id="B91FEAD0873FAA2045A4F85CDF00ADE2" box="[953,1120,1965,1992]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">C. claripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can easily be identified by the yellowish coloration of the wings, being dark brown on the distal half.
</paragraph>
